# Phase Status Interpretation

Phase status lives in `docs/phase_status/`.

Before editing:

- Read `docs/phase_status/README.md`.
- Read the phase status file that owns the requested subsystem.
- Read `docs/project-structure.md` for current target/app state.
- Prefer current source and CMake truth if docs disagree.

Checkbox meaning:

- `[x]` means implemented or verified enough to treat as current repo state.
- `[ ]` under `Started / Partial` means known partial work or known verification
  gap.
- `[ ]` under `Not Started` means planned but not implemented.
- `[ ]` under `Left To Do` means remaining work.
- `Finished Prerequisites From Earlier Phases` means prerequisites exist; it
  does not mean the future phase feature is implemented.

Phase discipline:

- Phases 1 through 7 are implemented in this checkout.
- Phase 8 networking/lobbies is next, but only when explicitly requested.
- Phase 9 polish/animation/audio/UI is future work, only when explicitly
  requested.
- Do not implement unchecked future-phase items just because they appear in a
  status file.

When completing work:

- After every repo-tracked change, check whether phase status changed.
- Update the matching phase status file when the work completes an unchecked
  item, starts or partially implements an item, removes or invalidates existing
  work, changes verification status, or changes a known gap.
- If no phase status file needs to change, explicitly say
  "No phase status change needed" in the final response.
- Only change `[ ]` to `[x]` when implementation and relevant verification are
  complete, or when current source/CMake truth proves the item was already done.
- If verification could not be performed, keep the item unchecked or document
  the verification gap.
- Do not remove unchecked items unless the plan or architecture intentionally
  changed.
